comments: Bol (ORL) is in the paint for less than three seconds when he is imminently exiting.

Bol (ORL) arm comes down and marginal contact occurs with Metu's (SAC) head follwing his shot attempt near the rim. Contact to an opponent's head/face can be deemed marginal when the result of a natural basketball move, provided the contact is not disproportionate or uncontrolled.
Barnes (SAC) reaches in and marginal contact occurs with Banchero's (ORL) front.
Barnes (SAC) contests the driving shot attempt and marginal body contact occurs with Banchero (ORL) after the release.
Fox (SAC) and Bol (ORL) engage and disengage with one another and marginal contact occurs off-ball in the post.
Bol (ORL) initiates contact with Fox's (SAC) arm, which affects his driving shot attempt.
Carter Jr. (ORL) brings his hands toward Barnes (SAC) and marginal contact occurs as he releases away to roll.
Carter Jr. (ORL) initiates marginal body contact with Sabonis (SAC) as he attempts to secure the pass.
Sabonis (SAC) saves the loose ball prior to stepping out of bounds.
Barnes (SAC) reaches in and initiates marginal arm contact with Suggs' (ORL) off arm during his drive.
Barnes (SAC) legally contests Suggs' (ORL) jump shot attempt.
Bol (ORL) is in the paint for longer than three seconds without imminently actively guarding an opponent.
Sabonis (SAC) and Carter Jr. (ORL) come together in pursuit of the loose ball and marginal contact occurs during the rebound.
Suggs (ORL) and Barnes (SAC) engage and disengage with one another and marginal contact occurs as they move around the screen.
Carter Jr. (ORL) touches the ball last before going out of bounds.
Sabonis (SAC) establishes his right foot as his pivot, he then lifts and re-plants his pivot foot prior to releasing the pass.
Sabonis (SAC) moves into Banchero's (ORL) lower body and initiates contact with his arm that affects his jump shot attempt.
Barnes (SAC) initiates illegal head contact with his shoulder to Carter Jr. (ORL) as engage during the pick.
Suggs (ORL) moves alongside Fox's (SAC) path and marginal body contact occurs during his drive.
Fox (SAC) establishes his right foot as his pivot, he then lifts and re-plants his pivot foot prior to releasing the ball.
Lyles (SAC) establishes a wide screening position and illegal contact occurs with Suggs' (ORL) lower body that affects his ability to defend.
Lyles (SAC) slightly slides to his left into Wanger's (ORL) path and initiates marginal body contact during shot attempt near the rim.
Bol (ORL) extends both hands forward and initiates marginal contact with Monk (SAC), attempting to take a foul.
Bol (ORL) commits a take foul on Monk (SAC).
Carter Jr. (ORL) commits a take foul on Sabonis (SAC).
Lyles (SAC) legally contests Wagner's (ORL) layup attempt.
Wagner (ORL) commits a take foul on Monk (SAC).
Fox (SAC) delivers body contact to Suggs (ORL) that affects his SQBR during the drive.
Wagner (ORL) extends both hands forward and initiates contact with Monk (SAC), which affects his SQBR.
